-- Rebekah Brooks to Learn If She’ll Be Charged Tomorrow, BBC Says
-- B y   L i n d s a y   F o r t a d o
-- 2012-05-14T17:29:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/rebekah-brooks-to-learn-if-she-ll-be-charged-tomorrow-bbc-says.html
Rebekah Brooks, the former chief
executive officer of News Corp.’s British unit, and her husband
will be told tomorrow whether they will be charged with
perverting the course of justice in the phone-hacking
investigation, the British Broadcasting Corp.  reported .  Brooks, her husband Charlie, and five others will be
informed about prosecutors’ decision tomorrow around 10:00 a.m.
when they report to police stations in London as part of their
bail conditions, the  BBC  said, citing sources.  Brooks’ spokesman,  David Wilson , and her lawyer, Stephen
Parkinson, didn’t immediately respond to requests for comment.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Lindsay Fortado in London at 
